  Decoherence Time | M 0.98 | C 0.99
    The speed at which off-diagonal terms vanish.
    This defines the "moment" of observation.

  Observation as Verdict (Retrospective) | M 0.94 | C 0.91 [opus]
    You cannot know DURING an interaction if observation occurred.
    You only know AFTER, when you verify info stayed scrambled.
    Observation isn't an EVENT. It's a VERDICT.
