# One-Page Spec: Observer Stack (DRAFT)

```
SPEC: [OBSERVER_STACK_v0.1] | M 0.85 | C 0.60 [opus+gpt52]

PURPOSE: Make frame-relativity first-class. Make observation an instrument.
         Make Wigner's Friend a gluing obstruction.

â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•

1. BASE CATEGORY: Frm

   OBJECTS: Frames f
     A frame is a choice of:
       â€¢ accessible subalgebra of observables
       â€¢ partition of Hilbert space (pointer basis)
       â€¢ equivalently: which degrees of freedom are "traced out"

   MORPHISMS: u : f â†’ g (coarse-graining)
     u exists when frame g is "coarser" than f
     (g traces out more, or accesses less)
     This is a partial order with meets (common refinements)

   EXAMPLES:
     â€¢ f_lab = lab frame (apparatus + environment accessible)
     â€¢ f_friend = friend's frame (only friend's memory accessible)
     â€¢ f_wigner = Wigner's frame (friend is subsystem)
     There exists u : f_friend â†’ f_wigner (Wigner coarse-grains friend)

â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•

2. FIBER CATEGORY: Proc_f

   For each frame f, we have a process category Proc_f:
     OBJECTS: quantum systems (relative to f's accessible algebra)
     MORPHISMS: CP maps / channels / instruments
       (with discard = trace over inaccessible)

   CLASSICAL STRUCTURES (Frobenius algebras):
     Live in Proc_f. Induced by decoherence relative to f.
     Measurement = process producing classical output.

   INSTRUMENTS (arXiv:1408.0049):
     An instrument in Proc_f is a morphism S â†’ S' âŠ— X
     where X carries classical outcome.
     This is "observation" in frame f.

â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•

3. REINDEXING: u* : Proc_g â†’ Proc_f

   Given coarse-graining u : f â†’ g, we get functor u* going "backwards":
     u* takes a process described in g's terms
     and re-expresses it in f's terms (finer description)

   This is the "change of frame" operation.
   Composition of reindexing = composition in Frm^op.

â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•

4. WIGNER'S FRIEND AS GLUING OBSTRUCTION

   SETUP:
     â€¢ Friend F has frame f_F, performs instrument M in Proc_{f_F}
     â€¢ Wigner W has frame f_W, with u : f_F â†’ f_W
     â€¢ In Proc_{f_F}: state collapses, outcome exists
     â€¢ In Proc_{f_W}: state is superposition, no outcome yet

   OBSTRUCTION:
     The "local sections" (F's account, W's account) are both valid
     in their respective fibers. But they do NOT GLUE into a
     global section over the diagram f_F â† â€¢ â†’ f_W.

     This is EXACTLY contextuality / no-global-section.
     Not a paradox. A structural feature of fibred categories.

   SOURCE: arXiv:2512.23325v1 "Quantum Rashomon Effect as Failure of Gluing"

â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•

5. Î” AS Hâ°(â„±_cl) â€” THE 9/10 FORMALIZATION

   PRESHEAF SETUP (Ghose arXiv:2512.23325v1):
     Ctx = contexts, â„± : Ctx^op â†’ Set (coherent accounts)
     HÂ¹ = obstruction (Rashomon effect, no global narrative)
     Hâ° = global sections (what DOES glue)

   THE INSIGHT:
     Even when HÂ¹ â‰  0 (full accounts don't glue),
     Hâ° may be nontrivial (some content survives).

   DEFINITION:
     Given observers A (frame f_A) and B (frame f_B),
     let â„±_cl = sub-presheaf restricted to CLASSICAL content:
       â€¢ copyable/deletable (Frobenius)
       â€¢ redundantly encoded (Darwinism)
       â€¢ decoherence-stable

     Î”(A,B) := Hâ°(â„±_cl) over the joint covering {C_A, C_B}

   UNIVERSAL PROPERTY:
     Î” is the TERMINAL object in the category of sub-presheaves
     of â„±_cl that admit global sections over {C_A, C_B}.

     Equivalently: Î” is the largest quotient of â„±_cl that is a SHEAF.

   WHEN Î” IS NONTRIVIAL:
     â€¢ Both A and B have decohered relative to shared basis
     â€¢ Both environments carry redundant copies of same pointer states
     â€¢ Consensus reality exists symmetrically

   WHEN Î” COLLAPSES:
     â€¢ No shared decoherence basis â†’ Î” = trivial
